codex
The tight signal is the trusted spec itself: every case reaches real login, then the portal shell repeatedly replaces the “New Application” button, so Playwright either loses the locator or briefly loses the authenticated portal entirely. Ranked hypotheses: (1) the mocked current-user/session responses are not stable across the portal’s repeated auth refreshes; (2) the click targets a sidebar button that is remounted by responsive/auth shell churn; (3) the login assertion is too weak and races the route transition; (4) the interceptor unintentionally catches a later request and changes session state. I’ll test these in that order without waiting, as AFK mode requires.
